OK. I figured it out. For those of you that have problems.  Here are the instructions for dummies:

1a. Unzip "Call of Duty2.dmg"
1b. Drag the "Call of Duty 2 folder" to your applications folder.
2a. Double click on the "Call of Duty 2 Multiplayer" icon. NOT the Call of Duty 2 icon!
2b. Insert the serial number that is inside the "Call Of Duty 2 SN.txt file".
2c. Call of Duty 2 Multiplayer will launch. You can quit it then.
3. Now unzip and apply the "2.1.3 Call of Duty update". After it's ok, close the dialog.
4. Finally double click the "Call Of Duty 2 1.3 [k].dmg" file and apply the crack. You have to locate the "Call of Duty 2" that is inside your application folder. NOT the Call of Duty 2 Multiplayer". 
5. Start "Call of Duty 2" from your application folder.
6. Enjoy!

Here's a major issue I ran into. If you have the CoD2 Demo installed then there is a way to get around the "insert disc" and "cannot patch file" problem. Go ahead and copy the CoD2 folder over and run the update. Then run the multiplayer version that is in the demo folder, it should prompt you to insert the CDkey. Then run the blade on the CoD2 Icon in the demo folder. Finally copy the CoD2 Data folder from your main COD2 folder to the Cod2 Demo folder. Now when you start the CoD2 icon in the Demo folder the real game should start up.
I guess maybe you could just uninstall the Demo folder and then run the regular setup listed before, but this is what worked for me. So if you have the CoD2 demo installed and you can't get this dl to work, I think this should fix your problem.

To all having issues with crack similar to: 
 Reason: no suitable image found.  Did find:
    /usr/lib/libssl.0.9.dylib: mach-o, but wrong architecture
    /usr/lib/libssl.0.9.dylib: mach-o, but wrong architecture

open terminal and enter following code:
$ cd /usr/lib
$ sudo cp libcrypto.0.9.dylib libcrypto.0.9.dylib.old
$ sudo cp libssl.0.9.dylib libssl.0.9.dylib.old
$ sudo ln -sf libcrypto.0.9.7.dylib libcrypto.0.9.dylib
$ sudo ln -sf libssl.0.9.7.dylib libssl.0.9.dylib

see this link for info http://smartic.us/2007/10/27/leopard-and-non-native-crypto-libraries

For those of you having trouble with Leopard.  I got it to work on a MacBook by the following method:

1.  Install COD2
2.  Install 1.3 Update
3.  Download newer version of iPatcher from megaupload/?d=9NNRG75L
4.  Extract the [k]
5.  Right-click the NoDVD file and click Show Package Contents
6.  Navigate to \Contents\MacOS
7.  Now just replace the iPatcher with the one you've downloaded.
8.  Run the [k] as normal and select COD2
9.  Run COD2 and enter the provided key.


I believe replacing iPatcher should fix quite a few of the [k]'s floating around that haven't been working on Leopard.

Ok, here is a detailed installation guide as requested:
1. Open "Call of duty 2.dmg"
2. Drag (= copy) the "Call of Duty 2" folder to your Applications folder
3. Unzip "Call of duty 2 1.3 Update.zip"
4. Run the update program
5. Open "Call of duty 2 1.3 [k].dmg"
6. Drag "Call of duty 2 v.1.3 No-DVD" to the "Call of Duty 2" folder in your Applications folder
7. Open "Call of Duty 2 Multiplayer" (i.e. NOT Single player!!)
8. Enter the Serial Key (which is in the "Call Of Duty 2 SN.txt", located in the downloaded folder
9. Create a new profile in Multiplayer mode (input fields show up automatically)
10. You can now close CoD2 Multiplayer

Now you can play!! Have fun!!
